Name: FileSystem
Description: Local file system tools (read/write/manage files and folders).
Version: 1.1

Overview:
This toolset exposes common file system operations: listing directories, reading
and writing files, editing files, creating folders, copying/moving paths,
deleting paths, and searching with glob patterns.

Commands:
- read_file_deprecated
  Read a text file (deprecated). Use read_text_file.
  Parameters:
  - path (string, required)

- read_text_file
  Read a text file.
  Parameters:
  - path (string, required)

- read_binary_file
  Read a binary file and return base64.
  Parameters:
  - path (string, required)

- read_multiple_files
  Read multiple text files.
  Parameters:
  - paths (array, required): List of file paths.

- list_directory
  List entries in a directory.
  Parameters:
  - path (string, optional): Directory path. Default '.'

- list_directory_recursive
  List entries recursively.
  Parameters:
  - path (string, optional)
  - max_depth (integer, optional)

- list_directory_with_sizes
  List entries in a directory with size in bytes.
  Parameters:
  - path (string, optional)

- directory_tree
  Return a directory tree up to max depth.
  Parameters:
  - path (string, optional): Directory path. Default '.'
  - max_depth (integer, optional): Default 3

- search_files
  Search for files matching a glob pattern.
  Parameters:
  - pattern (string, required): Glob pattern (e.g. '**/*.py')
  - base (string, optional): Base directory. Default '.'

- find_text_in_files
  Find text in files under a directory.
  Parameters:
  - base (string, required)
  - pattern (string, required)
  - query (string, required)
  - case_sensitive (boolean, optional)
  - max_matches (integer, optional)

- get_file_info
  Get file/folder metadata.
  Parameters:
  - path (string, required)

- list_allowed_directories
  List directories allowed for file operations.

Write/delete tools:
- write_file
  Write text to a file.
  Parameters:
  - path (string, required)
  - content (string, required)
  - overwrite (boolean, optional): Default true

- write_binary_file
  Write a binary file from base64.
  Parameters:
  - path (string, required)
  - content_b64 (string, required)
  - overwrite (boolean, optional): Default true

- edit_file
  Replace text in a file.
  Parameters:
  - path (string, required)
  - search (string, required)
  - replace (string, required)
  - count (integer, optional)

- head_file
  Get first N lines of a text file.
  Parameters:
  - path (string, required)
  - lines (integer, optional)

- tail_file
  Get last N lines of a text file.
  Parameters:
  - path (string, required)
  - lines (integer, optional)

- create_directory
  Create a directory (including parents).
  Parameters:
  - path (string, required)
  - exist_ok (boolean, optional): Default true

- move_file
  Move/rename a file or directory.
  Parameters:
  - src (string, required)
  - dst (string, required)
  - overwrite (boolean, optional): Default false

- delete_path
  Delete a file or directory.
  Parameters:
  - path (string, required)
  - recursive (boolean, optional): Default false

Other tools:
- copy_file_to_claude
  Copy a file to a local Claude drop folder.
  Parameters:
  - src (string, required)
  - dst_name (string, optional)
  - overwrite (boolean, optional): Default false

- copy_path
  Copy a file or directory.
  Parameters:
  - src (string, required)
  - dst (string, required)
  - overwrite (boolean, optional): Default false

Other utility:
- exists
  Check if a path exists.
  Parameters:
  - path (string, required)

- stat
  Get file or folder metadata.
  Parameters:
  - path (string, required)

- file_hash
  Compute a file hash.
  Parameters:
  - path (string, required)
  - algorithm (string, optional)

- fs_search
  Alias for search_files (filesystem).

Usage Examples:
- list_directory
- list_directory path="C:\\Users\\bismi"
- read_text_file path="C:\\temp\\notes.txt"
- read_multiple_files paths=["C:\\temp\\a.txt","C:\\temp\\b.txt"]
- write_file path="C:\\temp\\hello.txt" content="Hello"
- edit_file path="C:\\temp\\hello.txt" search="Hello" replace="Hi"
- create_directory path="C:\\temp\\newfolder"
- copy_path src="C:\\temp\\hello.txt" dst="C:\\temp\\hello_copy.txt"
- move_file src="C:\\temp\\hello_copy.txt" dst="C:\\temp\\moved.txt" overwrite=true
- delete_path path="C:\\temp\\moved.txt"
- search_files pattern="**/*.py" base="C:\\Users\\bismi\\Downloads\\noorRobot"
- fs_search pattern="**/*.py" base="C:\\Users\\bismi\\Downloads\\noorRobot"
- copy_file_to_claude src="C:\\temp\\notes.txt" dst_name="notes_copy.txt"

Behavior Notes:
- Paths are resolved to absolute paths.
- Text files are read/written using UTF-8.
- For folders, delete_path requires recursive=true to remove contents.

Security:
- Commands execute locally with the same permissions as the host process.

Dependencies:
- Python standard library (pathlib, shutil)
